.so ../bk-macros
.TH "bk help" "\*[BKVER]" %E% "\*(BC" "\*(UM"
.SH NAME
bk help \- get help for \*(BK commands
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bk help 
.[B] \-akp
.[OPTreq] \-f filename
.ARG specific-topic
.br
.B bk help topics
.SH DESCRIPTION
The 
.B bk help
command displays the online help for the specified command or topic.
Output gets displayed in the current command shell window.
See 
.B bk helptool
for information about the graphical interface for help.
.LP
A quick reference guide can be printed on Unix systems as
follows:
.DS
lpr \`bk bin\`/bk_refcard.ps
.DE
or on Windows/NT, click on the ``Quick Reference'' title in the start
menu, and assuming Acrobat is installed, the card will be displayed.
To print on Windows/NT, click on the ``file->print'' menu entry of
the Acrobat reader.
.LP
To get a list of all bk help topics use
.DS
.B bk help topics
.DE
.SH OPTIONS
.if t .TP .5i
.if n .TP .9i
.B \-a
Just search the docs for the string
.ARG topic .
This matches substrings and prints the topic followed by the matching
line.
.tp
.OPTreq \-f file
Use
.ARG file
as the helptext file.
.tp
.B \-k
Similar to
.BR -a ,
but only matches whole words.
.tp
.B \-p
disable the use of any pager just send the output to stdout.
.SH "FUTURE DIRECTIONS"
We will be adding a
.B bk man
command to format the man pages on the fly.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.SA helptool
.SH CATEGORY
